</article><!-- #post-## -->


			
				
<article id="post-459" class="post-459 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-news">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<!-- This is the output of the POST THUMBNAIL (if exists): REMOVED (h1 is clear:both) -->
		<!--<div class="entry-thumbnail">
			<img width="100" height="130" src="http://cml.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/uploads/cml/anandkumar.jpg" class="attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="" />		</div> -->
		<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://cml.ics.uci.edu/2015/01/anima-anandkumar-receives-afosr-young-investigator-award/" title="Permalink to Anandkumar receives AFOSR Young Investigator Award" rel="bookmark">Anandkumar receives AFOSR Young Investigator Award</a></h1>				<span class="entry-format genericon">Standard</span>			</header><!-- .entry-header -->

		<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Center member Prof. Anima Anandkumar received a 3-year grant, <i>Learning Mixed Membership Community Models: A Statistical and a Computational Framework</i>, from the Air Force Office of Scientific Research, as part of its <a href="http://www.wpafb.af.mil/news/story.asp?id=123436763">Young Investigator Research Program</a>.  The YIP is open to scientists and engineers who received their Ph.D. within the last five years, and show exceptional ability and promise for conducting basic research. Its objective is to foster creative basic research in science and engineering, enhance early career development of outstanding young investigators, and increase opportunities for the young investigators to recognize the Air Force mission and the related challenges in science and engineering.</p>
			</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
	<footer class="entry-meta">
				<a href="http://cml.ics.uci.edu/2015/01/anima-anandkumar-receives-afosr-young-investigator-award/" title="5:16 pm" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date genericon" datetime="2015-01-22T17:16:45+00:00">January 22, 2015</time></a>		
		
			</footer><!-- .entry-meta -->
</article><!-- #post-## -->


			
				
